After a string of successful collaborations, Tanzanian superstars Harmonize and Abigail Chams reunite for a deeply emotional and melodically rich new single titled “Lala.” This marks their fourth joint project, following fan-favorites “Closer,” “Leave Me Alone,” and “Me Too.”

Produced by Cukie Dady, “Lala” is a soulful of Bongo Fleva and soft Afro-pop, built around a tender theme of intimacy, emotional vulnerability, and timeless love. Harmonize pours his heart out as he sings about finally falling deeply in love expressing joy he’s never felt before and a desire to spend forever with his partner. His words, “You smell like honey, you're the only one,” paint a vivid picture of romantic admiration.

Abigail Chams responds with heartfelt emotion, sharing the internal conflict of trying to resist love but ultimately surrendering to it. Her vocals are soft yet striking as she confesses, “Why ghafla nakuita honey hivi mapenzi kitu gani, I don’t know why.” There’s a sense of honesty and youthful vulnerability in her delivery, making the record even more relatable.

The chorus, “Kifuani lalaa usinzie” (Lay on my chest, Fall asleep), becomes a comforting refrain a symbolic invitation into a safe space of love, peace, and emotional connection.

With unmatched chemistry and heartfelt storytelling, Harmonize and Abigail Chams once again deliver a song that resonates deeply. “Lala” is not just a duet it's a musical embrace that reminds listeners of the beauty of finding love, and the comfort of being seen, heard, and held.

snippet.description:
HAKAWII 
A soul-stirring anthem of trust, patience, and God’s perfect timing.

Performed by Kambua, written, produced, and directed by J Blessing, Hakawii reminds us that God is never late. He works in silence, shapes us like a potter with clay, and always shows up right on time.

🎧 Listen/Download here: https://onerpm.link/hakawii


Credits:
✍🏽 Written, Produced & Directed by: J Blessing
🎥 Video AD: Don Ibrah
💡 Lights & Set Design: Jerry
🏃🏽 Set Runner: Sebbi Humain
📜 Script: BBB
🎭 Casting Director: Dantez
🎚 Audio Production: Saint P
🎛 Mixed & Mastered: SoFresh
👥 Cast: Jane, Saint P, Tim Chege, Kambua Kids
🎬 Kambua Assistant: Lucy Sonnie
color grading : I-Director 
backup singers: Mbire and Joan 

🎵 HAKAWII – Kambua

(Swahili lyrics with English translation)

⸻

Nimeomba… nimesubiri
[I have prayed… I have waited]
Najua… Hakawii
[Now I know… He’s never late]
Hajawahi kuchelewa
[He has never been delayed]

⸻

VERSE 1

Sauti yako haijawahi nyamaza
[Your voice has never been silent]
Nilipoona kimya, Wewe ulikuwa ukitenda
[When I thought you were silent, You were at work]
Sikuona mlango ukifunguka
[I didn’t see the door open]
Lakini ulituma neema kabla ya mlango kuonekana
[But You sent grace before the door appeared]
Nifikiri umeniacha
[I thought You had left me]
Lakini ulikuwa karibu kuliko pumzi
[But You were closer than my breath]
Wakati wangu ulikuwa mpangoni
[My time was in Your plan]
Na jina lako likawa sahihi kwa saa zote
[And Your name proved right in every moment]

⸻

PRE-CHORUS 1

We ni Mungu wa ahadi
[You are the God of promise]
Na Simdogo wa miujiza
[And not limited in miracles]
Majira yako ni ya milele
[Your seasons are eternal]
Na moyo Wako hausahau
[And Your heart never forgets]

⸻

CHORUS

Hakawii… Mungu wangu hakawii
[Never late… My God is never late]
Kila chozi lina majira
[Every tear has its timing]
Na kilio kina sauti Yake
[And every cry carries His voice]
Hakawii… Hakawii
[Never late… Never late]
Yuko sahihi – hata nisipoelewa
[He’s always on time – even when I don’t understand]

⸻

VERSE 2

Wengine walicheka nikiwa nangoja
[Some laughed while I was waiting]
Wakaniambia, “mbona hajibu kama yupo?”
[They asked, “Why doesn’t He answer if He’s real?”]
Lakini sasa naona kwa macho ya roho
[But now I see with the eyes of the spirit]
Hakuna hasara kwa anayemngojea Bwana
[There’s no loss in waiting on the Lord]
Nililia bila majibu
[I cried with no answers]
Nikafunga bila kuona ishara
[I fasted without seeing signs]
Lakini moyo wangu haukuwahi kuwa pweke
[But my heart was never alone]
Kwa sababu polepole, alinijenga kuwa shahidi
[Because slowly, He was building me up to be a witness]

⸻

PRE-CHORUS 2

Wakati Wake… ni ushuhuda wangu
[His timing… is my testimony]
Haandiki kwa haraka
[He does not write in haste]
Ahadi za nizamilele
[His promises are eternal]
Hakawii
[Never late]
Na anajua kila dakika ya machozi yangu
[And He knows every minute of my tears]

⸻

CHORUS – REPEAT

Kila chozi lina majira
[Every tear has its season]
Na kilio kina sauti Yake
[And every cry carries His voice]

[Never late… Never late]
Yuko sahihi – hata nisipoelewa
[He is right on time – even when I don’t understand]

[Never late… Never late]
Yuko sahihi – hata nisipoelewa
